# Next.js Frontend Conventions

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router, static export (`output: "export"`)
- React 19 functional components
- Tailwind CSS + `cn()` from `@/lib/utils`
- shadcn-style paths: `@/components`, `@/hooks`, `@/lib`

## Component patterns

```tsx
// Client components with browser APIs or hooks
"use client";

// Server components by default in app/ — no directive needed
import type { Metadata } from "next";
```

- Dynamic import WebGL/shader components: `dynamic(..., { ssr: false })`
- Colocate component-specific logic in hooks under `web/hooks/`
- Global animations/tokens in `web/app/globals.css`

## Styling

- Prefer Tailwind utilities; use `cn()` for conditional classes
- Dark theme: `<html className="dark">` in layout
- Reveal animations: `reveal-section`, `data-hero-on-view` + `useLandingEffects`

## Static export constraints

- No `getServerSideProps`, API routes, or server actions requiring runtime
- Images: `unoptimized: true` in next.config
- basePath from `NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH` for GitHub Pages asset URLs

## File naming

- Components: `kebab-case.tsx` exporting `PascalCase` function
- Hooks: `use-*.ts`
- Keep landing page sections in `landing-page-inner.tsx`

## Imports

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils";
import { SomeIcon } from "lucide-react";
```
